title: Capital 150th: traffic & travel advice
text:
Topix › Pacific Travel › Capital 150th: traffic & travel advice Capital 150th: traffic & travel advice 1 hr ago Read more: Wellington City Council 
Wellington is celebrating 150 years as the Capital City this weekend - and the celebrations may cause some traffic disruption - especially for the 'Open House: Treasures of Wellington' open days on Saturday and Sunday. Motorists may encounter heavy traffic and heavy pedestrian traffic - at some 'hotspots' around the CBD on both days as some 42 'Treasures of Wellington' are opened free for public visits between 10am and 5pm. Start the conversation, or Read more at Wellington City Council.
